@kramasamy the Scheduler is passed the URL that the uploader outputs in the Runtime Config, since we're sending the Docker tag as the URI here (technically it's not a URI but...) the Scheduler can export it. In the case of the Aurora scheduler you have:
`...
String heronCoreReleasePkgURI = Context.corePackageUri(config);
String topologyPkgURI = Runtime.topologyPackageUri(runtime).toString();

auroraProperties.put("CORE_PACKAGE_URI", heronCoreReleasePkgURI);
auroraProperties.put("TOPOLOGY_PACKAGE_URI", topologyPkgURI);
...`

So the heron.aurora file could download the image by doing something like `docker pull {{TOPOLOGY_PACKAGE_URI}}`. Aurora will handle the templating.

And re: Slack chris.pardy@gmail.com

